# i++ solution
# Read a digit character ('0'-'9') and output its increment (with wraparound)

# Read the input character
A<I

# Convert from ASCII to numeric value by subtracting '0'
# But we can't do arithmetic! So we need a lookup table

# Create a lookup table at location 48-58 (ASCII codes for '0'-'9')
# Location 48 will contain 49 ('1')
# Location 49 will contain 50 ('2')
# ...
# Location 57 will contain 48 ('0' - wraparound)

[48]<49
[49]<50
[50]<51
[51]<52
[52]<53
[53]<54
[54]<55
[55]<56
[56]<57
[57]<48

# Now we can use the input character as an index
# A contains the ASCII value of the input digit
# We look up location [A] to get the incremented value

# Output the result
O<[A]

# Halt
Z<1